s\n|colspan='2' align=center| Alan Burkitt\n|colspan='1' align=center| Stephane Anelli\n|colspan='1' align=center| Graeme Henderson\n|Jake Weinstein\n|-\n! Pat Denning\n|colspan='1' align=center| James Congdon\n|Gary Holcombe\n|colspan='1' align=center| Bob Sessions\n|colspan='1' align=center| Richard Muenz\n|Daren Kelly\n|colspan='1' align=center| Steven Houghton\n|colspan='1' align=center| Stuart Ramsey\n|colspan='1' align=center| Matthew McKenna\n|colspan='1' align=center| Norman Bowman\n|Ryan K. Bailer\n|-\n! Abner Dillon\n|colspan='1' align=center| Don Crabtree\n|Iggie Wolfington\n|colspan='1' align=center| Ralph Lawton\n|colspan='1' align=center| Michael McCarty\n|Paul Ainsley\n|colspan='2' align=center| Steve Fortune\n|colspan='1' align=center| Teddy Kempner\n|colspan='1' align=center| Bruce Montague\n|Cliff Bemis\n|-\n! Mac\n|colspan='1' align=center| Stan Page\n|[[Lonnie Burr]]\n|colspan='1' align=center| Brent Verdon\n|colspan='1' align=center| Allen Fitzpatrick\n|Michael Fitzpatrick\n|colspan='1' align=center| David Lucas\n|colspan='1' align=center| \n|colspan='1' align=center| Scott Emerson\n|colspan='1' align=center| Mark McKerracher\n|\n|-\n! Ann \u201cAnytime Annie\u201d Reilly\n|colspan='1' align=center| Karen Pruczik\n|Rose Scudder\n|colspan='1' align=center| Carol Ball\n|colspan='1' align=center| Mylinda Hill\n|Alana Salvatore\n|colspan='2' align=center| Lisa Donmall Reeve\n|colspan='1' align=center| Emma Kate Nelson\n|colspan='1' align=center| Emma Caffrey\n|Megan McLaughlin\n|-\n! Lorraine Flemming\n|colspan='1' align=center| Ginny King\n|Marla Singer\n|colspan='1' align=center| Felicity Lee\n|colspan='1' align=center| Megan Sikora\n|Kristen Gaetz\n|colspan='1' align=center| Pippa Raine\n|colspan='1' align=center| Ebony Molina\n|colspan='1' align=center| Charlie Allen\n|colspan='1' align=center| Ella Martine\n|Melissa Schott\n|-\n! Phyllis Dale\n|colspan='1' align=center| Jeri Kansas\n|Nancy Bickel\n|colspan='1' align=center| Catherine Terry\n|colspan='1' align=center| Catherine Wreford\n|Angela Kahle\n|colspan='1' align=center| Kate Nelson\n|colspan='1' align=center| Lisa Ritchie\n|colspan='1' align=center| Chantel Bellew\n|colspan='1' align=center| Clare Rickard\n|Lily Lewis\n|-\n! Oscar\n|colspan='1' align=center| Robert Colston\n|Bob Gorman\n|colspan='1' align=center| Art Day\n|colspan='1' align=center| [[Billy Stritch]]\n|Tom Judson\n|colspan='1' align=center| Peter McCarthy\n|colspan='1' align=center| \n|colspan='1' align=center| Barnaby Thompson\n|colspan='1' align=center| Paul Knight\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Musical numbers==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n;Act I\n*\u201cOverture\u201d \u2013 Orchestra\n*\u201cAudition\u201d \u2013 Dancers\n*\u201cShadow Waltz\u201d \u2013 Maggie, Dorothy, and Girls\n*\u201cYoung and Healthy\u201d \u2013 Billy and Peggy\n*\u201cShadow Waltz (Reprise)\u201d \u2013 Dorothy\n*\u201cGo into Your Dance\u201d \u2013 Maggie, Peggy, Annie, Phyllis, Lorraine, Gladys, and Andy\n*\u201c[[You're Getting to Be a Habit with Me]]\u201d \u2013 Dorothy\n*\u201cGetting Out of Town\u201d \u2013 Maggie, Bert, Pat, and Chorus\n*\u201c[[We're in the Money]]\u201d \u2013 Annie, Phyllis, Lorraine, Gladys, Peggy, Billy, and Chorus\n*\u201cDames\u201d \u2013 Billy and Chorus\n*\"[[Keep Young and Beautiful]]/Dames Reprise\" - Bert, Maggie and Ensemble\n*\"[[I Only Have Eyes for You]]\" - Dorothy and Billy\n*\u201cI Know Now\u201d \u2013 Dorothy, Chorus and Billy\n*\u201c[[Boulevard of Broken Dreams (Al Dubin song)|Boulevard of Broken Dreams]]\u201d \u2013 Dorothy\n*\u201cAct One Finale\u201d \u2013 Dorothy and Orchestra\n{{col-break}}\n\n;Act II\n*\u201cEntr\u2019acte\u201d \u2013 Orchestra\n*\u201cThere\u2019s a Sunny Side to Every Situation\u201d \u2013 Annie and Chorus\n*\u201c[[Lullaby of Broadway (song)|Lullaby of Broadway]]\u201d \u2013 Julian and Company\n*\u201c[[About a Quarter to Nine]]\u201d \u2013 Dorothy and Peggy\n*\"With Plenty of Money and You\" - Men Ensemble\n*\u201c[[Shuffle Off to Buffalo]]\u201d \u2013 Maggie, Bert, Annie, and Girls\n*\u201c[[Forty-Second Street]]\u201d \u2013 Peggy with Dancing Company\n*\u201cForty-Second Street (Reprise)\u201d \u2013 Julian\n*\u201cFinale Ultimo\u201d \u2013 Full Company and Orchestra\n{{col-end}}\n\n:''In the 2001 revival, a reprise of \"Getting Out of Town\" followed \"Lullaby of Broadway\" and \"With Plenty of Money and You\"  followed \"[[About a Quarter to Nine]]\", \"Keep Young and Beautiful\" followed \"Dames\", and \"I Only Have Eyes for You\" followed \"We're in the Money\".\n\n:''For the 2017 West End revival, \u201cBoulevard of Broken Dreams\u201d was added into the show for [[Sheena Easton]].\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n===Original Broadway production===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\"| Year\n! width=\"20%\"| Award Ceremony\n! width=\"40%\"| Category\n! width=\"20%\"| Nominee\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n! width=\"5%\"| Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"13\" align=\"center\"| 1981\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[Drama Desk Award]]\n| colspan=\"2\"| [[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Musical|Outstanding Musical]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" align=\"center\"|<ref>[https://archive.is/20080704130258/http://www.dramadesk.com/1980_1981dd.html \"Drama Desk, 1980-1981\"] dramadesk.com, accessed April 8, 2011</ref>\n|-\n| [[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Featured Actor in a Musical|Outstanding Featured Actor in a Musical]]\n| [[Lee Roy Reams]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Choreography|Outstanding Choreography]]\n| [[Gower Champion]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Costume Design|Outstanding Costume Design]]\n| [[Theoni V. Aldredge]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"| [[Theatre World Award]]\n| Wanda Richert\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>[http://www.theatreworldawards.org/award.html \"Previous Theatre World Award Recipients, 1980\u201381\"] theatreworldawards.org, accessed April 9, 2011</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\"| [[Tony Award]]\n| colspan=\"2\"| [[Tony 