t ever manager. {{As of|2012|1}}, the El Salvador national football team has presented itself with 60 managers in the national team. It is reported that all 3 titles ([[1943 CCCF Championship|1943]],<ref name=\"CCCF 1943\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/cccf43.html|title=CCCF Championship 1943 (San Salvador, El Salvador, Dec 5\u201319)|date=2002-08-06|accessdate=2010-11-11|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]}}</ref> [[Football at the 1954 Central American and Caribbean Games|1954]]<ref name=\"CAG 1954\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/cag54.html|title=Central American and Caribbean Games 1954 (Mexico)|date=2007-04-02|accessdate=2010-11-11|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]}}</ref> and [[Football at the 2002 Central American and Caribbean Games|2002]]<ref name=\"CAG 2002\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/cag02.html|title=Central American and Caribbean Games 2002 (El Salvador)|date=2005-12-21|accessdate=2010-11-11|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]}}</ref>) have been won by Salvadoran born managers. [[Conrado Miranda]] has managed in 4 different occasions and [[Armando Contreras Palma]] in 3. [[Chilean people|Chilean]] [[Hern\u00e1n Carrasco Vivanco|Hern\u00e1n Vivanco]] was manager when El Salvador competed at their first [[1970 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]].<ref name=\"Managers\">{{cite web|url=http://www.elbaloncuscatleco.com/directores.html|title=Directores  |date=2008-01-24|accessdate=2010-11-11|publisher=El Balon Cuscatleco |language=Spanish |trans-title=Managers}}</ref> [[Mauricio Alonso Rodr\u00edguez|Mauricio Rodr\u00edguez]] managed to qualify El Salvador to another [[1982 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]]. Rodiguez participated at the 1970 FIFA World Cup.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Name\n!Years\n|-\n| {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Mark Scott Thompson]]\n| 1930\u20131935\n|-\n| {{Flagicon|SPA}} [[Pablo Ferre El\u00edas]]\n| 1935\u20131938\n|-\n| {{Flagicon|Chile}} {{F